CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper March 16, 1957, pg. 27, reads: "Victory Smiles - The smile was the thing in Oliver High School's dressing room last Friday night at the Pitt Field House after they had defeated Peabody for the Pittsburgh high school championship. Seated in the midst of his victorious cagers is Coach Harry Norris Sigel. Calvin Fowler, third from left, back row, is Oliver's chief scorer. The other Oliver ace is Don Clisby, seated to the left of his coach. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Oliver High School basketball team with sixteen players including Calvin Fowler third from left in back, and Don Clisby third from left in middle, and coach Harry Norris Sigel, cheering in locker room
